---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base>
  <!-- PANEL 1 · white · hero split: copy left, photo right -->
  <section class="panel">
    <div class="container split hero-split">
      <div>
        <p class="opening-note">People Make Sense</p>
        <h1>Most people try to change their lives. I help them understand why their lives make sense.</h1>
        <p class="lead">
          Whether you're trying to change your own life or help a team work better together, it starts in the same
          place: not with trying harder, but with understanding why the hard thing keeps happening.
        </p>
        <div class="btn-row" style="margin-top:1.75rem;">
          <a href="/personal-work" class="btn">Start Personal Work</a>
          <a href="/professional-work" class="btn btn-outline">Bring This to Your Team</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="photo-block" style="--block:var(--gold);">
        <div class="photo-slot portrait" style="--tint:#ffffff;">
          <span>Photo: Candace, composed portrait, natural light, one teal or gold element in frame</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="hairline-gold" />

  <!-- PANEL 2 · white · single column, generous margins -->
  <section class="panel">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p>You already know how this goes. The promise to speak up next time. The apology you didn't owe. The meeting that ended in agreement and fell apart before lunch.</p>
      <p>You've read the books and tried the strategies. You can describe the problem in detail, which is somehow the most frustrating part, because understanding it from the outside hasn't changed it.</p>
      <p>The pattern you can't seem to break is doing a job. It makes sense once you understand what it's been accomplishing, even if it no longer fits the life you're living. That's why trying harder rarely works. You can't out-muscle something you haven't understood.</p>
      <p>So we don't start with strategies. We start by understanding what the pattern has been doing for you. Sometimes that's enough. Sometimes that understanding opens the door to deeper work. Either way, change stops feeling like a fight and starts feeling like a choice.</p>
      <blockquote class="pullquote" style="--accent:var(--teal);">The behavior is real. It just isn't the whole story.</blockquote>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PANEL 3 · tint #E9F3F1 · two columns, recognition rows -->
  <section class="panel tint-band" style="--tint:#E9F3F1;">
    <div class="container">
      <h3 class="center" style="margin-bottom:2.5rem;">Different rooms. Same thing underneath.</h3>
      <div class="grid-2" style="max-width:1000px; margin-inline:auto;">
        <div>
          <h4>In your life</h4>
          <ul class="recognition-rows" style="--dot:#56B6B1;">
            <li>You replay conversations at night, rewriting what you said.</li>
            <li>You agreed to something yesterday that you resented by this morning.</li>
            <li>You can feel yourself disappearing into a relationship, and you keep choosing it anyway.</li>
            <li>You achieved the things. You're still waiting for the feeling that was supposed to come with them.</li>
            <li>You know exactly what you'd tell a friend in your situation. You just can't take the advice.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>At work</h4>
          <ul class="recognition-rows" style="--dot:#006073;">
            <li>The meeting ends, and the real meeting starts in the parking lot.</li>
            <li>You said it clearly. They heard something else. Now there are two stories.</li>
            <li>Everyone agrees on the goal and keeps colliding on the way there.</li>
            <li>There's a person everyone has quietly learned to work around, and it's costing more than anyone says out loud.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PANEL 4 · white · two large clickable cards side by side -->
  <section class="panel">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid-2" style="max-width:900px; margin-inline:auto;">
        <a href="/personal-work" class="card washes" style="--rule:#56B6B1; --wash:#E9F3F1;">
          <h3>Personal Work</h3>
          <p>Maybe you've been working on this for years. Maybe you woke up one day and realized something isn't right. Either way, the problem probably isn't what you think it is. And it probably isn't you.</p>
          <span class="card-link" style="--rule:#56B6B1;">Explore Personal Work →</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/professional-work" class="card washes" style="--rule:#006073; --wash:#CCD8DE;">
          <h3>Professional Work</h3>
          <p>Organizations don't struggle because they lack smart people. They struggle because smart people keep misunderstanding each other. When people finally make sense, communication, leadership, and performance all change.</p>
          <span class="card-link" style="--rule:#006073;">Bring This to Your Team →</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <hr class="hairline-gold" />

  <!-- PANEL 5 · white · 50/50 split: photo left, copy right -->
  <section class="panel">
    <div class="container split">
      <div class="photo-block" style="--block:#E9F3F1;">
        <div class="photo">
          <img src="/img/candace-portrait.jpg" alt="Candace Malmstrom, warm and direct, in natural light" width="1100" height="1375" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>Meet Candace</h3>
        <p>I spend my week in two very different rooms: counseling individuals, and working with organizations. Each one sharpens the other. Sitting with people one at a time is how I know what actually moves them, not in theory, in practice, and that's what I bring to companies. And working inside real teams every week is how the individual work stays practical instead of philosophical.</p>
        <a href="/about" class="arrow-link" style="--accent:var(--teal);">More about me →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PANEL 6 · statement band · Teal, white text · the boldest moment on the site -->
  <section class="panel statement-band center">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="statement-words">People Make Sense</p>
      <hr class="gold-rule" />
      <p class="statement-sub">In patterns. In relationships. In teams. In the places we keep getting stuck.</p>
      <p class="statement-quote">"Everything makes sense now. I know what to do. And I feel capable of doing it."</p>
      <p class="statement-after">That's the moment we're after.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PANEL 7 · white · centered close -->
  <section class="panel center">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <h3>Start here</h3>
      <p>
        You don't have to know what's wrong.<br />
        You don't have to know where to begin.<br />
        You only have to be willing to understand what's actually happening.<br />
        We'll figure out the rest together.
      </p>
      <div class="btn-row" style="justify-content:center; margin-top:1.75rem;">
        <a href="/personal-work" class="btn">Start Personal Work</a>
        <a href="/professional-work" class="btn btn-outline">Bring This to Your Team</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<style>
  .hero-split { align-items: center; }
  .hero-split h1 { max-width: 19ch; }

  /* the brand's opening note: letterspaced Gold caps, one step larger than an eyebrow */
  .opening-note {
    font-family: var(--sans);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.26em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--gold);
    margin: 0 0 1.1rem;
  }

  .statement-words {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: clamp(2.6rem, 7vw, 4.6rem);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin: 0 0 0.4rem;
  }
  .statement-sub { font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1.8vw, 1.25rem); margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .statement-quote {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 2.4vw, 1.7rem);
    line-height: 1.4;
    max-width: 32ch;
    margin: 0 auto 1.1rem;
  }
  .statement-after { margin: 0; opacity: 0.9; }
</style>
